#fire-http
[![Build Status](https://secure.travis-ci.org/firejs/fire-http.png)](http://travis-ci.org/firejs/fire-http)

Http expressions for [fire.js](https://github.com/firejs/fire)
***

## Installing

### using NPM

    npm install fire-http

## Expressions

* @Http
* @Http.Headers.Authorization

## Usage

`Sending a GET`

    "@Http(GET)": {
		"uri": "http://127.0.0.1:3600/"
	}

or with dynamic method:

    "@Http": {
		"method": "GET",
		"uri": "http://127.0.0.1:3600/"
	}

`Sending a POST with Body`

    "@Http(POST)": {
		uri: "http://127.0.0.1:3603/",
		body: "Content of the Body"
    }

`Headers`

    "@Http(GET)": {
		uri: "http://127.0.0.1:3604/",
		headers: {
			"CustomHeader": "Stuff"
		}
    }

`Basic Authorization`

	"@Http(GET)": {
		uri: "http://127.0.0.1:3604/",
		headers: {
			"Authorization": {
				"@Http.Headers.Authorization(Basic)": {
					"user": "Chuck",
					"password": "SuperChuck"
				}
			}
		}
    }


or 

    "@Http(GET)": {
		uri: "http://127.0.0.1:3604/",
		headers: {
			"Authorization": {
				"@Http.Headers.Authorization": {
					"scheme": "Basic",
					"user": "Chuck",
					"password": "SuperChuck"
				}
			}
		}
	}

## Cloning the Repository

    git clone git://github.com/firejs/fire-http.git

### Tests

    make run-tests

